line_1: No Air of Wit, no beauteous Grace I boast;
line_2: My Charms are native Innocence at most.

line_1: My Charms are native Innocence at most.
line_2: No Air of Wit, no beauteous Grace I boast;

line_1: Alike thy Pencil, and thy Numbers charm,
line_2: Glad ev'ry Eye, and ev'ry Bosom warm.

line_1: Glad ev'ry Eye, and ev'ry Bosom warm.
line_2: Alike thy Pencil, and thy Numbers charm,

line_1: Mature in Years, if e'er I chance to tread,
line_2: Where Vice, triumphant, rears aloft her Head,

line_1: Where Vice, triumphant, rears aloft her Head,
line_2: Mature in Years, if e'er I chance to tread,

line_1: Ev'n there the Paths of Virtue I'll pursue,
line_2: And own my fair and kind Director You.
